cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.IR 

This paper is about creating a corpus of counter-arguments using natural language processing techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves crowdworkers and machine learning models, which suggests that it could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves analyzing the data and constructing a baseline model, which could fall under sub-categories such as cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
